      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In classic Devolver Digital fashion, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Card Shark",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " provides a unique gameplay experience that acts as a breath of fresh air in a medium that can often feel stale and repetitive. Being able to revel in the life of an 18th-century card hustler provides its own unique sense of satisfaction and I love that the game aims to keep things fresh with the occasional sword fencing duel. Despite the somewhat disjointed plot progression, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Card Shark",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is an absolute blast and a game that I'd be quick to recommend to someone who's on the lookout for a fresh new experience.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
